        "answer_count": 4,
        "title": "Java - indentify the String which is have special character at the last",
        "body": "<p>Having a list of String while iterating am trying to identify the last character of the String containing any special character.<\/p>\n\n<p>for eg:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Apple,\nApple\nApple(\nApples.\nApples\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Expected Result :<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Apple\nApples\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Please find my code below, am just replacing the special character with \"\" (empty) as of now., But i want to remove the string itself.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (TermSuggestion.Entry entry : termSuggestion.getEntries()) { \n    for (TermSuggestion.Entry.Option option : entry) { \n        String suggestText = option.getText().string();\n        String result = suggestText.replaceAll(\"[-+.^:,]()\",\"\");\n        System.out.println(\"Print String---&gt;  \"+result);\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "question_id": 51702360,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "string"
        ],
        "score": -1,
        "accepted_answer_id": 51702447,
        "closed_reason": "Needs more focus",
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 143,
        "last_edit_date": 1573313803
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d99204bcce923f40f5c72b7f80121644?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2139538,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1898563,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1898563/michael",
                "reputation": 44485,
                "display_name": "Michael",
                "accept_rate": 78
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540095,
            "creation_date": 1533540095,
            "body": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/lang/Character.html#isAlphabetic(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Character.isAlphabetic<\/code><\/a> to work out whether its a special character or not. You can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#charAt(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>String.charAt<\/code><\/a> to get the last character.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (TermSuggestion.Entry entry : termSuggestion.getEntries())\n{ \n    for (TermSuggestion.Entry.Option option : entry)\n    { \n        String suggestText = option.getText().string();\n        if (Character.isAlphabetic(suggestText.charAt(suggestText.length()))\n        {\n            System.out.println(\"Print String---&gt;  \"+result);\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702447,
            "question_id": 51702360
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5ddfd9fbd9f21ef824a8425a649ff5a2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1940767,
