                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540198,
            "creation_date": 1533539955,
            "body": "<p>You can use this regex <code>.*[a-z]$<\/code> to filter only words that end with a small case/lower case character.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702415,
            "question_id": 51702360,
            "last_edit_date": 1533540198
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/272533323503817/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 14000572,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 10112322,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10112322/memo",
                "reputation": 1938,
                "display_name": "memo"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540235,
            "creation_date": 1533540235,
            "body": "<p>To <em>remove<\/em> the string, first of all your collection must be modifiable. In your case it's  <code>termSuggestion<\/code>, so make sure it is, or make a copy if not.\nThen, use an <code>Iterator<\/code> and iterate by calling <code>hasNext()<\/code> and <code>next()<\/code>. Once you hit the string you want to remove, call the <code>remove()<\/code> method. See the Iterator documentation: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Iterator.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Iterator.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702483,
            "question_id": 51702360
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-3rAgz6oRNFI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAE8/zUWNbWkPJSY/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 12210830,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 8912667,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8912667/fabien-mifsud",
                "reputation": 353,
                "display_name": "Fabien MIFSUD"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540535,
            "creation_date": 1533540535,
            "body": "<p>Following code with Streams and apache.commons.lang3.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; strings = Arrays.asList(\"Apple\", \"Apple\", \"Apple\", \"Apples.\", \"Apples\");\nString[] alphabet = {\"a\", \"b\", \"c\", \"d\", \"e\", \"f\", \"g\", \"h\", \"i\", \"j\", \"k\", \"l\", \"m\", \"n\", \"o\", \"p\", \"q\", \"r\", \"s\", \"t\", \"u\", \"v\", \"w\", \"x\", \"y\", \"z\"};\nList&lt;String&gt; result = strings.stream().filter(item -&gt; StringUtils.endsWithAny(item, alphabet)).distinct().collect(Collectors.toList());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702548,
            "question_id": 51702360
        }
